<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-09-29T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-09-29T10:00:00-05:00" n="348" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d348">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BC Indonesia/9–2949:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Embassy in the
                                        Netherlands</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">secret   priority</hi>
                                    <lb/>
                                    <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                                    </gloss>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-09-29T10:00:00-05:00">September 29, 1949—10 a. m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>834. Eyes only for Cochran from Butterworth. In fulfillment my
                                promise to keep you serviced, I think I shd let you know before
                                weekend <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss>-Dutch conference
                                    (<gloss target="#t_Hicus1">Hicus</gloss> 40<note n="1" xml:id="d348fn1">Telegram 849, September 28, not
                                printed.</note>) not inconsiderable importance, which has not been
                                dimmed by Burma experience, is attached here to incorporation
                                specific safeguards against confiscatory taxation, etc., for foreign
                                including Amer investments <gloss target="#t_USI1">USI</gloss> as
                                you envisaged in Cochran Plan. Our thought from this distance is
                                that ability to influence <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss>s to
                                take fixed policy of enlightened character is now.
                                [Butterworth.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>